title: How have waiting times after an urgent referral changed?
analysis_commentary: The percentage of people being seen within two weeks had remained largely consistent, between 95% and 96%, since Quarter 3 2009/10. However, since Quarter 3 2013/14 this has decreased and was at an all-time low of 93.5% in Quarter 1 2014/15. It has since increased again to 94.7% but in Quarter 1 2015/16 come back down to a low of 93.6%.
